  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "A pioneering method in this category is SegMatch (Dubé et al. 2017) which is the first to present real-time loop-closure detection and localization in 3D point clouds (see Fig. 8).",
    "SegMatch first segments the raw 3D point cloud into sets of point clusters and then uses post-segment features encoded by a CNN on the clusters to find place matches.",
    "Finally, a geometric verification step is applied to turn the candidate matches into place recognition candidates.",
    "Since segmentation provides a good compromise between local and global descriptions by combining their advantages while mitigating their disadvantages, this method not only reduces the matching time but also decreases the likelihood of false matches.",
    "In a follow-up work, Dubé et al. (2018) proposed an incremental segment-based localization for 3D-PCPR, which utilizes an incremental segmentation algorithm to track the evolution of single segments."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "A pioneering method in this category is SegMatch (Dubé et al. 2017) which is the first to present real-time loop-closure detection and localization in 3D point clouds (see Fig. 8).",
